    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-05-20T20:36:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-05-20T20:36:00-05:00" n="1144"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1144">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.6363/74.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Special Agent <persName type="from">Carothers</persName> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                    <note n="98" xml:id="d1144fn98">Communicated to the Secretary of the Navy and
                        the British Ambassador May 23, 1914.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Extract.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Torreon</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-05-20T19:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 20, 1914, 7 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Carranza has no objection to the establishing of the wireless communication as
                    requested by you May 8, 9 p.m. He has telegraphed General Gonzalez at Tampico to
                    see if there is any local reason <pb facs="0820" n="704" xml:id="pg_704"/>
                    against same. Expects reply today. He has further telegraphed Gonzalez to
                    furnish full and adequate protection to foreigners and has informed him that
                    many American employees will return to take care of oil wells.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Carothers</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
